      "id": "PopularPost69707",
      "post_content": "@drunyon: Of course! [Seal of Fire](/Pages/Card/Details.aspx?name=Seal of Fire)! Why didn't I think of that?  \n  \nYeah, I think the best way to pull this off is with a [Lightning Bolt](/Pages/Card/Details.aspx?name=Lightning Bolt), [Shard Volley](/Pages/Card/Details.aspx?name=Shard Volley), or even [Sonic Seizure](/Pages/Card/Details.aspx?name=Sonic Seizure) in response to the triggered ability. That way he gets +1/+1 counters from the damage, and is therefore basically a 4/4 for four that deals 3 damage and forces you to discard a card upon entering play. Which is a good deal, in my opinion. Cause, you know, [Hidden Horror](/Pages/Card/Details.aspx?name=Hidden Horror) is good, and so is ![Red](/Handlers/Image.ashx?size=small&name=R&type=symbol) for 3 damage.   \n  \nOr you could free-cast [Fireblast](/Pages/Card/Details.aspx?name=Fireblast) in response, but two mountains can be risky if you're really just doing it to make your [War Elemental](/Pages/Card/Details.aspx?name=War Elemental) a 5/5 for ![Red](/Handlers/Image.ashx?size=small&name=R&type=symbol)![Red](/Handlers/Image.ashx?size=small&name=R&type=symbol)![Red](/Handlers/Image.ashx?size=small&name=R&type=symbol) after you're out of [Ball Lightning](/Pages/Card/Details.aspx?name=Ball Lightning)s. Oh, wait, that's kinda good, isn't it?  \n  \nI still wish he cost ![Red](/Handlers/Image.ashx?size=small&name=R&type=symbol)![Red](/Handlers/Image.ashx?size=small&name=R&type=symbol) or were a 0/0 with Bloodthirst 1 for ![Red](/Handlers/Image.ashx?size=small&name=R&type=symbol)![Red](/Handlers/Image.ashx?size=small&name=R&type=symbol)![Red](/Handlers/Image.ashx?size=small&name=R&type=symbol) instead of his comes-into-play ability (or Bloodthirst X... [(see all)](javascript:void(0);)",
      "posted_by": "Ragamander",
      "html": "<div class=\"post evenItem\" id=\"PopularPost69707\" style=\"background-color: rgba(255,255,255,0.08);\">\n<span class=\"postContent\" id=\"ctl00_ctl00_ctl00_MainContent_SubContent_SubContent_popularPosts_postsRepeater_ctl06_post\">@drunyon: Of course! <a class=\"autoCard\" data:cardname=\"Seal of Fire\" href=\"/Pages/Card/Details.aspx?name=Seal of Fire\">Seal of Fire</a>! Why didn't I think of that?<br/><br/>Yeah, I think the best way to pull this off is with a <a class=\"autoCard\" data:cardname=\"Lightning Bolt\" href=\"/Pages/Card/Details.aspx?name=Lightning Bolt\">Lightning Bolt</a>, <a class=\"autoCard\" data:cardname=\"Shard Volley\" href=\"/Pages/Card/Details.aspx?name=Shard Volley\">Shard Volley</a>, or even <a class=\"autoCard\" data:cardname=\"Sonic Seizure\" href=\"/Pages/Card/Details.aspx?name=Sonic Seizure\">Sonic Seizure</a> in response to the triggered ability. That way he gets +1/+1 counters from the damage, and is therefore basically a 4/4 for four that deals 3 damage and forces you to discard a card upon entering play. Which is a good deal, in my opinion. Cause, you know, <a class=\"autoCard\" data:cardname=\"Hidden Horror\" href=\"/Pages/Card/Details.aspx?name=Hidden Horror\">Hidden Horror</a> is good, and so is <img align=\"absbottom\" alt=\"Red\" src=\"/Handlers/Image.ashx?size=small&amp;name=R&amp;type=symbol\"/> for 3 damage. <br/><br/>Or you could free-cast <a class=\"autoCard\" data:cardname=\"Fireblast\" href=\"/Pages/Card/Details.aspx?name=Fireblast\">Fireblast</a> in response, but two mountains can be risky if you're really just doing it to make your <a class=\"autoCard\" data:cardname=\"War Elemental\" href=\"/Pages/Card/Details.aspx?name=War Elemental\">War Elemental</a> a 5/5 for <img align=\"absbottom\" alt=\"Red\" src=\"/Handlers/Image.ashx?size=small&amp;name=R&amp;type=symbol\"/><img align=\"absbottom\" alt=\"Red\" src=\"/Handlers/Image.ashx?size=small&amp;name=R&amp;type=symbol\"/><img align=\"absbottom\" alt=\"Red\" src=\"/Handlers/Image.ashx?size=small&amp;name=R&amp;type=symbol\"/> after you're out of <a class=\"autoCard\" data:cardname=\"Ball Lightning\" href=\"/Pages/Card/Details.aspx?name=Ball Lightning\">Ball Lightning</a>s. Oh, wait, that's kinda good, isn't it?<br/><br/>I still wish he cost <img align=\"absbottom\" alt=\"Red\" src=\"/Handlers/Image.ashx?size=small&amp;name=R&amp;type=symbol\"/><img align=\"absbottom\" alt=\"Red\" src=\"/Handlers/Image.ashx?size=small&amp;name=R&amp;type=symbol\"/> or were a 0/0 with Bloodthirst 1 for <img align=\"absbottom\" alt=\"Red\" src=\"/Handlers/Image.ashx?size=small&amp;name=R&amp;type=symbol\"/><img align=\"absbottom\" alt=\"Red\" src=\"/Handlers/Image.ashx?size=small&amp;name=R&amp;type=symbol\"/><img align=\"absbottom\" alt=\"Red\" src=\"/Handlers/Image.ashx?size=small&amp;name=R&amp;type=symbol\"/> instead of his comes-into-play ability (or Bloodthirst X... <a href=\"javascript:void(0);\" onclick=\"ExpandPost(event, this, 69707)\">(see all)</a></span>\n<div class=\"postDetails\" id=\"ctl00_ctl00_ctl00_MainContent_SubContent_SubContent_popularPosts_postsRepeater_ctl06_postDetails\" style=\"padding-top: 5px;\">\n<div class=\"reportAbuse\">\n<a href=\"../../Classes/Controls/#\" id=\"ctl00_ctl00_ctl00_MainContent_SubContent_SubContent_popularPosts_postsRepeater_ctl06_reportAbuseLink\" onclick=\"HandleReportPost(this, '69707'); return false;\">\r\n                                    Report Abuse</a>\u00a0\u00a0\r\n                                    \r\n                            </div>\n<div class=\"postedBy\">\r\n                                Posted By: \r\n                                <span id=\"PostedBy13722\">Ragamander</span>\r\n                                (7/28/2010 6:17:43 AM)\r\n                            </div>\n<div class=\"postRating\">\n<div class=\"postRatingLabel\">\r\n                                    Rating:\u00a0\r\n                                </div>\n<div style=\"float: left;\">\n<div class=\"starRating\" id=\"ctl00_ctl00_ctl00_MainContent_SubContent_SubContent_popularPosts_postsRepeater_ctl06_postRating_starRating\"><img alt=\"0.5\" src=\"../../Images/Stars/LeftSolidSmall.png\"/><img alt=\"1.0\" src=\"../../Images/Stars/RightSolidSmall.png\"/><img alt=\"1.5\" src=\"../../Images/Stars/LeftSolidSmall.png\"/><img alt=\"2.0\" src=\"../../Images/Stars/RightSolidSmall.png\"/><img alt=\"2.5\" src=\"../../Images/Stars/LeftSolidSmall.png\"/><img alt=\"3.0\" src=\"../../Images/Stars/RightSolidSmall.png\"/><img alt=\"3.5\" src=\"../../Images/Stars/LeftSolidSmall.png\"/><img alt=\"4.0\" src=\"../../Images/Stars/RightSolidSmall.png\"/><img alt=\"4.5\" src=\"../../Images/Stars/LeftSolidSmall.png\"/><img alt=\"5.0\" src=\"../../Images/Stars/RightClearSmall.png\"/>\n<br/>\n</div>\n</div>\n<br class=\"clear\"/>\n</div>\n<div class=\"postRating\">\n<div class=\"postRatingLabel\">\r\n                                    \u00a0\r\n                                </div>\n<div style=\"float: left;\">\n</div>\n<br class=\"clear\"/>\n</div>\n<br class=\"clear\"/>\n</div>\n</div>"
